Package com.intel.icecp.core.channels

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ChannelProvider
    Define a common interface for building a Channel; since network IO may involve some one-time setup and tear down, the helper methods ChannelProvider.start(ScheduledExecutorService, Configuration) and ChannelProvider.stop() are present and will be called before (or after, in the case of stop()) any channels are built.
    HistoricalChannel<T extends Message>  
    OnLatest<T extends Message>
    Allow dynamic generation of messages when a channel is queried for its latest message
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ChannelBase<T extends Message>
    Base implementation of a channel; extend this in transport-specific sub-classes to simplify development.
    OnLatest.Response<T extends Message>
    Data structure for returning generated messages and their attributes as a response to an OnLatest request
    Token<T>
    Capture the type parameters of a generic class for use in serializing generic messages.
